idge|publisher=Cambridge University Press|ref=harv}}\n: {{cite book|last=Beckett|first=Francis|year=2007|title=Clem Attlee|publisher=Politico's|ref=harv}}\n: {{cite book|last1=Benn|first1=Tony|last2=Mullin|first2=Chris|year=1979|title=Arguments for Socialism|publisher=J. Cape|ref=harv}}\n: {{cite book|last=Berberoglu|first=Berch|year=2018|title=The Palgrave Handbook of Social Movements, Revolution, and Social Transformation|publisher=Springer|isbn=9783319923543|ref=harv}}\n: {{cite book|last=Berman|first=Sheri|year=1998|title=The Social Democratic Moment: Ideas and Politics in the Making of Interwar Europe|location=Cambridge, Massachusetts|publisher=Harvard University Press|isbn=9780674442610|ref=harv}}\n: {{cite book|last=Berman|first=Sheri|year=2006|title=The Primacy of Politics: Social Democracy and the Making of Europe's Twentieth Century|publisher=Cambridge University Press|isbn=9780521817998|ref=harv}}\n: {{cite book|last=Bernstein|first=Eduard|translator-last=Harvey|translator-first=Edith C.|year=1907|orig-year=1899|url=https://www.marxists.org/reference/archive/bernstein/works/1899/evsoc/index.htm|title=Evolutionary Socialism|publisher=Independent Labour Party|ref=harv}}\n: {{cite book|last=Bevan|first=Aneurin|year=1952|title=In Place of Fear|location=New York|publisher=Simon and Schuster|ref=harv}}\n: {{cite book|last=Bevan|first=Aneurin|year=1961|title=In Place of Fear|edition=2nd|publisher=MacGibbon and Kee|ref=harv}}\n: {{cite book|last1=Boggs|first1=Carl|last2=Plotke|first2=David|year=1980|title=Politics of Eurocommunism|publisher=Black Rose Books|isbn=9780919618312|ref=harv}}\n: {{cite book|last=Bookchin|first=Murray|year=1998|title=The Third Revolution: Popular Movements in the Revolutionary Era|volume=2|location=London|publisher=Cassell|isbn=9780304335930|ref=harv}}\n: {{cite book|editor-last1=Borragan|editor-first1=Nieves Perez-Solorzano|editor-last2=Cini|editor-first2=Michelle|year=2013|title=European Union Politics|chapter=Glossary|publisher=Oxford University Press|isbn=9780199694754|ref=harv}}\n: {{cite book|last=Bracke|first=Maud|year=2013|title=Which Socialism, Whose D\u00e9tente?: West European Communism and the Czechoslovak Crisis of 1968|publisher=Central European University Press|isbn=9786155211263|ref=harv}}\n: {{cite book|last1=Brandal|first1=Nik|last2=Bratberg|first2=\u00d8ivind|last3=Thorsen|first3=Dag Einar|date=21 February 2013|title=The Nordic Model of Social Democracy|publisher=Springer|isbn=9781137013279|ref=harv}}\n: {{cite book|last=Braudel|first=Fernand|year=1979|title=The Wheels of Commerce: Civilization and Capitalism 15th\u201318th Century|publisher=Harper & Row|ref=harv}}\n: {{cite book|last=Brockway|first=Fenner|year=1980|title=Britain's First Socialists|ref=harv}}\n: {{cite book|editor-last=Brown|editor-first=Archie|year=2004|title=The Demise of Marxism-Leninism in Russia|publisher=Springer|isbn=9780333651247|ref=harv}}\n: {{cite book|last=Brown|first=Susan Love|year=1997|chapter=The Free Market as Salvation from Government|title=Meanings of the Market: The Free Market in Western Culture|publisher=Berg Publishers|ref=harv}}\n: {{cite book|last=Busky|first=Donald F.|year=2000|title=Democratic Socialism: A Global Survey|location=Westport, Connecticut|publisher=Praeger Publishers|isbn=9780275968861|ref=harv}}\n: {{cite book|editor-last1=Cahill|editor-first1=Damien|editor-last2=Cooper|editor-first2=Melinda|editor-last3=Konings|editor-first3=Martijn|editor-last4=Primrose|editor-first4=David|year=2018|title=The SAGE Handbook of Neoliberalism|publisher=SAGE Publications|isbn=9781526415974|ref=harv}}\n: {{cite book|last=Calossi|first=Enrico|year=2016|title=Anti-Austerity Left Parties in the European Union. Competition, Coordination, Integration|location=Pisa|publisher=Pisa University Press|isbn=9788867416653|ref=harv}}\n: {{cite book|last=Cammack|first=Paul|year=2004|chapter=Giddens's Way with Words|editor1-last=Hale|editor1-first=Sarah|editor2-last=Leggett|editor2-first=Will|editor3-last=Ma